    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-06-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="754"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d754">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Choate</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 27, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 350.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my dispatch No. 344, of the 20th
                    instant, and to your telegram in reply, dated the 22d instant, both relative to
                    the terms of payment for Mr. Geldart’s shipment on the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Mashona</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Beatrice</hi>, I have the honor to
                    inclose herewith the copy of a note which I have addressed to Lord Salisbury on
                    the subject dated yesterday.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph H. Choate.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-26">
                                <hi rend="italic">June 26, 1900</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: With respect to my interview with your
                        lordship on the 19th instant, in reference to my note of the 9th instant and
                        to previous correspondence, upon the subject of the detention by the British
                        authorities in South Africa of merchandise shipped by Mr. R. W. Geldart from
                        New York to Delagoa Bay, under instructions from my Government, I have the
                        honor to state that Mr. Geldart considers that $1,000 would protect him from
                        the loss with respect to the shipments on board the <hi rend="italic"
                            >Mashona</hi>, and that he would accept that amount as full payment of
                        his claim, and further that he would accept $575 for his shipments (beer and
                        lard) on board the <hi rend="italic">Beatrice.</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>I should therefore be glad to hear your lordship’s views upon the subject and
                        whether the proposition above stated will be acceptable to Her Majesty’s
                        Government.</p>
                    <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Joseph H. Choate.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
